On Wednesday, Aug 07, 2002, at 08:25AM, TR Gesell <trgesell(-at-)compuserve.com> wrote:

>1.  When pulling off the flexible couplings to the heat exchangers, I got a
>face full of something which looks a lot like asbestos.  Does anyone have
>any idea if a '77 would have had asbestos in the heating system?
.  I'm considering a high-end rebuild from Gary's VW in San Diego, because

There is a pair of white asbestos collars between the flexible hose and the heater flapper boxes as seen here:

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/78%20Camper/26%2DEngineOutBack.JPG

Do not breathe, handle with gloves, etc.  It's evil stuff especially if it's disturbed.

If you search the archives you'll find mention that this unavailable item can be replaced with a vanagon part.  If yours is falling apart badly it may not survive putting the engine back together.

